nc%C3%A9%2C%20who%20also%20is%20a%20seasonal%20worker.%20The%20jobs%20she%20works%20are%20hired%20through%20contractors%2C%20not%20directly%20through%20the%20National%20Park%20Service.%20This%20story%20has%20been%20edited%20for%20length%20and%20clarity.%20Business%20Insider%20has%20verified%20her%20employment%20and%20pay.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20had%20honestly%20never%20even%20visited%20a%20national%20park%20before%20I%20moved%20to%20one.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20was%20living%20in%20Texas%20and%20was%20struggling%20to%20figure%20out%20my%20passion.%20I%20actually%20dropped%20out%20of%20college%20twice.%20The%20first%20time%20I%20was%20going%20to%20school%20to%20be%20an%20elementary%20school%20teacher.%20When%20I%20went%20back%20I%20was%20studying%20hospitality.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOne%20of%20my%20friends%20took%20the%20advice%20of%20a%20friend's%20father%20who%20told%20her%2C%20%26quot%3BIf%20you're%20ever%20lost%20in%20life%2C%20if%20you%20don't%20know%20what%20to%20do%2C%20go%20scoop%20ice%20cream%20in%20Yellowstone.%26quot%3B%20She%20got%20a%20job%20in%20Yosemite%2C%20and%20when%20she%20came%20to%20visit%20me%20I%20had%20never%20seen%20her%20so%20happy.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20followed%20her%20lead%2C%20left%20school%2C%20and%20got%20a%20job%20in%20Death%20Valley%20as%20a%20restaurant%20host.%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3EI%20was%2021%20or%2022%20then.%20Now%20I'm%2029.%20I%20have%20been%20doing%20seasonal%20work%20ever%20since%2C%20most%20often%20as%20a%20server%20at%20hotels%20or%20restaurants.%20I've%20worked%20at%20places%20like%20Zion%2C%20Glacier%2C%20Yosemite%2C%20and%20the%20Grand%20Canyon%2C%20and%20now%20I%20am%20back%20in%20Death%20Valley.%20I've%20been%20a%20server%20for%20the%20past%20seven%20years%20and%20I%20really%20love%20it.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20discovered%20my%20passion%20for%20the%20outdoors%20through%20seasonal%20work.%20I%20do%20love%20my%20job%20in%20hospitality%2C%20but%20to%20me%20it's%20a%20means%20to%20be%20where%20I%20want%20to%20be.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22dabf6acc-14db-4b44-bcd2-574b4ce21146%5C%22%3ESeasonal%20work%20often%20means%20moving%20every%20four%20to%20six%20months%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EI've%20worked%20for%20different%20companies%20that%20operate%20inside%20the%20parks.%20There%20are%20some%20people%20who%20stick%20to%20one%20company%2C%20which%20has%20its%20perks%20because%20you%20can%20easily%20transfer%20property%20to%20property.%20And%20then%20there%20are%20some%20people%20who%20just%20pick%20a%20destination%20and%20then%20whoever%20is%20operating%20there%20ends%20up%20becoming%20their%20employer.%20For%20the%20past%20couple%20years%2C%20I%20have%20stuck%20to%20transferring%20through%20the%20same%20company%2C%20Xanterra.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMost%20of%20our%20contracts%20are%20anywhere%20from%20four%20to%20six%20months.%20Once%20you%20start%20seasonal%20work%2C%20it's%20like%20you%20get%20bitten%20by%20the%20bug.%20After%20four%20months%2C%20I'm%20itching%20to%20go%20somewhere%20new.%20For%20finding%20jobs%2C%20a%20good%20resource%20that%20a%20lot%20of%20us%20use%20is%20a%20site%20called%20CoolWorks.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%224032%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Woman%20outdoors%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F670f0154a70318649282a988%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%223024%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EWright%20has%20worked%20in%20Moab%2C%20Utah%2C%20near%20Canyonlands%20National%20Park.%3Cp%3EMegan%20Wright%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22beea465d-8a9b-4de4-8a9d-5f428b75339e%5C%22%3EHousing%20and%20pay%20can%20vary%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EPay%20in%20the%20seasonal%20circuit%20varies%20pretty%20dramatically.%20Since%20I%20am%20a%20server%2C%20the%20majority%20of%20my%20wage%20comes%20from%20tips.%20Each%20state%20also%20has%20their%20own%20%26quot%3Bserver%20wage%2C%26quot%3B%20so%20I%20might%20make%20a%20fair%20hourly%20rate%20in%20California%2C%20and%20much%20lower%20somewhere%20like%20Utah.%20This%20extreme%20change%20in%20pay%20rate%20also%20has%20a%20huge%20influence%20on%20where%20I%20choose%20to%20work.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3E%5BEditor's%20note%3A%20Wright%20has%20made%20anywhere%20from%20%2410.30%20to%20%2416.65%20per%20hour%20plus%20tips%20in%20some%20of%20her%20most%20recent%20jobs%2C%20according%20to%20employment%20contracts%20she%20shared%20with%20Business%20Insider.%20She%20noted%20that%20she%20makes%20most%20of%20her%20money%20in%20tips%20and%20makes%20more%20during%20busy%20seasons.%5D%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWe%20typically%20have%20employer-provided%20housing%2C%20which%20can%20vary%20on%20the%20quality.%20Some%20have%20really%20nice%20housing%20where%20you're%20in%20basically%20a%20studio%20apartment%20with%20your%20own%20bathroom%20and%20kitchenette.%20Other%20places%20are%20similar%20to%20a%20college%20dorm%20with%20a%20shared%20hallway%20bathroom.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt's%20a%20totally%20different%20lifestyle.%20There's%20dorm-style%20living.%20You%20live%20with%20your%20coworkers%2C%20basically.%20You%20see%20each%20other%20every%20single%20day.%20There%20is%20no%20escape.%20That's%20good%20and%20bad.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt's%20incredibly%20easy%20to%20make%20friends%20in%20seasonal%20work.%20We're%20all%20on%20this%20journey%20together%20and%20you%20have%20a%20deep%20understanding%20of%20one%20another.%20You%20make%20really%20close%20friendships.%20It%20feels%20more%20like%20a%20family.%20Everybody%20bands%20together%20and%20is%20supportive.%20We%20always%20joke%20that%20you've%20got%20to%20be%20a%20little%20weird%20to%20get%20into%20seasonal%20work.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI've%20known%20so%20many%20people%20who've%20met%20their%20partners%20in%20seasonal%20work.%20I%20met%20my%20fianc%C3%A9%20at%20the%20Grand%20Canyon%20and%20he%20was%20also%20doing%20seasonal%20work.%20Now%20we%20move%20around%20to%20new%20places%20together.%20It's%20nice%20to%20have%20a%20partner%20with%20you%20while%20you%20travel.%20Another%20perk%20is%20that%20a%20lot%20of%20these%20pl